The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 London, March 7: Tata Motors is expected to sign a memorandum of understanding to buy Ford Motors Jaguar and Land Rover in the next two weeks, a labour union negotiator said on Friday. There are no roadblocks holding back the deal, but negotiations have proved complex, said Dave Osborne, national secretary for vehicle building at the Unite union.                             
	 Mumbai, March 7: India Cements is aiming to invest in coal mines abroad and acquire bulk cargo carriers to transport coal to achieve the twin objectives of securing quality coal at a reasonable price and avoiding the impact of ever increasing shipping freight.                             
	 New Delhi, March 7: DLF Assets is planning to raise about Rs 2,000 crore through pre-IPO placements by the end of this month to fund various projects, but may delay its public offer in Singapore because of turbulent stock market conditions across the world.                            
	 New Delhi, March 7: The size of Indias economy will grow to 90 per cent of the US by 2050, with China becoming even bigger than the United States, a PricewaterhouseCoopers (PwC) report said.                            
	 New Delhi, March 7: ArcelorMittal is open to securing independent mines other than Chiria, which has seen many claimants, including SAIL.                                                                                                                           
